  "cross_sheet_notes": "This is sheet 5 ('PLC overview') of Sensor Control Unit 2, drawing 31971 (=LA2/+SCU2). Power (24V from 4.4/X24V.3, 0V from 4.6/X0V.3, PE from 3.2/PE.5DA0) arrives from other sheets. I/O module details continue on /5.4 (A101), /6.4 (A102/A103/A104) and /7.4 (A105/A106). Ethernet extends off-station to +SCU1/5.3 and +SCU3/5.2 via the two Metz media converters.",
  "brief": {
    "sheet_title": "Sheet 5 'PLC overview' of Sensor Control Unit 2 (SCU2) — the Beckhoff EtherCAT I/O station and its two fiber/LAN media converters that link the panel to remote sensor units SCU1 and SCU3.",
    "purpose": "This sheet lays out the EtherCAT I/O rack: a bus coupler (-5/A100, read as EK1100) with a string of terminal modules — one 8-channel digital output (EL2008), two 8-channel digital inputs (EL1008), a 4-channel PT100/RTD temperature input (EL3204), two 2-channel 120...230VAC digital inputs (EL1722), and an end terminal (EL9011). The coupler is powered by 24V and 0V (from cross-references on other sheets) and earthed via PE. Its two Ethernet ports (ETH In / ETH Out) run to two Metz Connect media converters (-5/U1, -5/U2), which carry the network out over cables -W5445 and -W5473 ('LAN outdoor') to the remote units SCU1 and SCU3. The actual per-channel wiring is on the referenced detail sheets (/5.4, /6.4, /7.4).",
    "key_signals": [
      {
        "signal": "Network link to remote sensor unit SCU1",
        "tag": "-W5445",
        "terminal": "-5/A100 ETH In via converter -5/U1",
        "destination": "+SCU1/5.3 (-ETH.D)",
        "confidence": 0.8
      },
      {
        "signal": "Network link to remote sensor unit SCU3 (outdoor LAN run)",
        "tag": "-W5473 (LAN outdoor)",
