    "troubleshooting_example": "Suppose SCU1 drops off the network. Check the link at two distinct points. First, at the coupler side of converter -5/U1: confirm the copper Ethernet from -5/A100 'ETH In' is live/linked at -5/U1. If there is no copper link there, the fault is between the coupler and U1 (patch/port), not the outdoor run. Second, if the copper side at -5/U1 is good but the converter's outgoing side / cable -W5445 shows no link at the far end (+SCU1/5.3, -ETH.D), the fault is the media converter -5/U1 or the -W5445 run to SCU1. A dead copper link at U1 points to the coupler/patch; a good copper link with no far-end link isolates the converter or its outbound cable. Note: this sheet is only the physical/overview layout — it does not show the control logic, so it cannot tell you how the PLC application reacts to the loss.",
